{
  "text": "Theoretical and empirical evidence suggest that the price of a bottled wine primarily depends on production costs, quality, reputation and objective, easily observable product characteristics [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ). According to a study conducted by [CITATION_4] , price was a very important wine choice criterion for all respondents. Reasoning that scarcity, the quality of grape varieties or prestige pricing increases the financial value of wine [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] ), we hypothesize:",
